The protest was organised by the Coal Transportation Forum representing companies that transport coal which is opposed to government signing the Independent Power Producer agreement. They say this will lead to mine closures and job losses.Tshwane Metro Police spokesperson Senior Superintendent Isaac Mahamba said the truck drivers had planned to march to the Union Buildings. At this stage our focus is to unblock the roads and get free flow of traffic." Action would then be taken against those responsible he said.Pretoria - N1 North: #ProtestAction RT @JustinKennerley @TrafficSA N1N after Rigel has been closed by what appears to be truck drivers. pic.twitter.com/2f92RTXhCX Rob Byrne (@TrafficSA) March 1, 2017Pretoria - N1 North: #ProtestAction RT @JustinKennerley @TrafficSA N1N after Rigel has been closed by what appears to be truck drivers. pic.twitter.com/2f92RTXhCX We know the organisers we have their details. They came to apply for a permit said Mahamba.Mahamba said they had agreed with the protest organisers that they be allowed to travel in trucks and motor vehicles to Marabastad from where they would march to the Union Buildings. We came to a compromise that they can come into the city with trucks and motor vehicles driving individually stop at Marabastad park the trucks get into the motor vehicles and go straight to the Union Buildings from 10am until around 2pm said Mahamba.Centurion - N14 North, #TruckDriverProtest through Centurion - LONG QUEUE towards PTA, via @Gee_Motsepe pic.twitter.com/OheJWJsveZ Rob Byrne (@TrafficSA) March 1, 2017Centurion - N14 North, #TruckDriverProtest through Centurion - LONG QUEUE towards PTA, via @Gee_Motsepe pic.twitter.com/OheJWJsveZ But for them to wake up this morning be on trucks park in the middle of the road as is being alleged we didn't approve that he said.Sephiwe Montlha a councillor from Shoshanguve said he had been sitting in traffic for an 90 minutes and there was no sign that the situation would improve."The trucks are just standing the middle of the road. I've passed two trucks but there are eight in front of me and I can't see past that " he said.#PTATraffic (U/D) Protest action: N1 northbound after Rigel Ave, all lanes blocked. Please use alternative routes. pic.twitter.com/Ox1exlQAsP Netstar Traffic (@netstartraffic) March 1, 2017#PTATraffic (U/D) Protest action: N1 northbound after Rigel Ave, all lanes blocked. Please use alternative routes. pic.twitter.com/Ox1exlQAsPMontlha said the trucks were driving at no more than 20km/h. Some truck drivers left their vehicles in the middle of the road."The driver is [getting] in and out of his truck just doing things deliberately for the convoy not to move " he said."One guy insulted him very angry. Everybody was very angry even taxi drivers."@TrafficSA Truck Driver Protest at the Fountains Circle in Pretoria, into the CBD pic.twitter.com/xYg2LGX9SM MaXhamela (@PYekaniMakhubu) March 1, 2017@TrafficSA Truck Driver Protest at the Fountains Circle in Pretoria, into the CBD pic.twitter.com/xYg2LGX9SM"The situation is bad. They say there are trucks coming from Witbank and other areas of Limpopo who are going to marches in town " Montlha said."I don't see any metro police on the road. Normally they would be here but today there is no-one. Something is not right " he said.Motorists also took to social media to vent their frustration at the gridlock. Chaos around @CityTshwane as many coal tipper trucks block roads in some kind of protest.. #truckstrike @Wheels24 @ewnupdates pic.twitter.com/0yL597y6qa Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) March 1, 2017Chaos around @CityTshwane as many coal tipper trucks block roads in some kind of protest.. #truckstrike @Wheels24 @ewnupdates pic.twitter.com/0yL597y6qa#TruckStrike I get it ... but some of us need to workpic.twitter.com/HKgxM2sw7z #TheBookOfChad (@NormaMansoor) March 1, 2017#TruckStrike I get it ... but some of us need to workpic.twitter.com/HKgxM2sw7zThis is a developing story.